Trim the root and the dark green top from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then
thinly slice widthways.

Halve the @chestnut mushrooms{150}.

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1}(drained and rinsed).

== Cheesy Ciabatta ==

Halve the @ciabatta{1} (as if you were making a sandwich) and spread the
@onion marmalade{20%g} on the cut sides.

Cut the @goat's cheese{125} into 3 slices per person. Place the goat's cheese
slices on top of each ciabatta half.

Pop onto a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your #oven{} for
~{10-12%mins}.

== Fricassee ==

Meanwhile, heat the @Flora Original{20%g} in a large #saucepan{} over
medium-high heat.

When the Flora has melted, add the mushrooms and cook, stirring frequently, for
~{3%mins}.

Add the leeks and cook until softened, ~{2-3%mins}, adding a splash more oil if
needed.

Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp} and the @water{100%ml}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{112.5%g} and bring to a simmer, then mix in the
@wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp} and the lentils.

Add the @baby spinach{125%g} a handful at a time and allow to wilt,
~{2-3%mins}. Remove the pan from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Finely chop the @chives{1/2}(finely chopped) (or use #scissors{} if it's easier).

Remove the cheesy ciabatta from the oven and get ready to serve.

Taste the fricassee and add @salt{} and @pepper{} as necessary. Share between your
#bowls{}.

Cut the ciabatta at an angle so you have 2 pieces per person and place on top of
the fricassee.

Finish with a sprinkling of chives. ENJOY!